Multi-Robot Coordination with Overhead Vision System

Micro-Controller Python Image Processing PID Control NRF Communication

Developed and tested a system for simultaneous control of four autonomous robots within a shared environment, using an overhead camera as the sole sensory input. Robots operated without onboard sensors or cameras, fully dependent on real-time navigation and control instructions from a central PC server.

Key Achievements

  • Centralized overhead vision-based navigation and PID Control
  • Real-time wireless communication via NRF modules
  • Coordinated multi-robot path planning and collision avoidance
